        "subject": "LU-3660 acl: support mount option \"noacl\" for zfs",
        "message": "LU-3660 acl: support mount option \"noacl\" for zfs\n\nzfs parse mount option in zpl layer, but osd-zfs calls dmu\ndirectly, to support mount option \"noacl\", parse it in\nmount.lustre, and osd-zfs set a flag at mount time, then later\nall ACL operations will check whether ACL is enabled, otherwise\n-EOPNOTSUPP is returned.\n\nadd sanity test 103b for \"noacl\" mount.\n\nSigned-off-by: Lai Siyao <lai.siyao@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I654db02facb64d51151ed0d7ee1cd7a0ba41904a\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
